    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.62"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">62</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI
                        <lb/>
                    COLUMBIA
                        <lb/>
                        
                    COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE
                        <lb/>
                    DEPARTMENT OF SPEECH AND DRAMATIC ART</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>                
                    <dateline>September 25, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>209 Jesse</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>                
                <p>The "Sea Nymph" is so lovely that she moves me deeply. The long flowing lines of her body, the still innocence of her face, the cascade of her hair--all of it forms a melody. I have a kind of feeling that if I am very quiet, she may wake.</p> 
                
                <p>To have you cast the little figure that Mrs. Neihardt conceived and shaped makes the gift priceless. How can I find words to thank you for a gift like this? I love it; I have pride in it an am humble before it. Thank you.</p>
                
                <p>Will you come in for a visit with Bill and me when you feel in the mood to talk with people this year?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Frances</signed>
                
                    <signed>Frances L. McCurdy</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
